@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Squax" where you want 
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed.

                             How to play?

  You move tiles by clicking on any large tile that is surrounded by 8
other tiles, empty spaces or smaller square tiles. Each surrounding tile
of the same size will rotate by 90 degrees clockwise around the clicked
tile, as the following example shows:

 a.b       ..a       .c.
 .*.   ->  c*.   ->  .*.  etc.
 .c.       ..b       b.a

  ...where the letters 'a', 'b' and 'c' are the tiles, the '*' is the
clicked tile and the dots ('.') are the empty spaces.

  Note that you must click on the large tiles, as clicking on the small
square tiles or empty spaces (the small dots) will have no effect.

  To help you in the game, small square tiles indicate where the large
tiles have to go. You can also click on the 'Figure' button, which will
briefly show the game pattern that you have to match.

  You can restart a game anytime by clicking on the @{b}New Game@{ub} button
(or with the Right-Amiga + "N" key combination).

  Have fun!

@endnode

